  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nSee https://discord.com/channels/593655374469660673/621838504955084830/907737187288743956\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/light-client/src/server/LightClientUpdater.ts#L170\r\n\r\nIt appears that our finalized state, passed to `onFinalized` is always dialed to the epoch, rather than the post-state of the finalized checkpoint block.\r\nSo when there's skip slot(s) at the end of the epoch, we're going to be proving from a different state. The next sync committee branch will be wrong.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nThe next sync committee branch should be created against the post-state of the finalized checkpoint block.",
